cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SI. 

This paper deals with mechanism design for a game-theoretic problem involving the allocation of resources (facility locations) among selfish agents. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The problem also involves algorithmic aspects, which suggests categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of penalties and distances in the problem formulation may also suggest categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
